Visiting from Houston first time in Chicago with my wife for our anniversary and wanted to try this place out. I never do reviews but for this guy had to. Ryan was working alone and was helping every one from being on the register to making the burgers and even having to make Milkshakes. Yes a lot of us can just say well that's his job but for people in the food industry know it's never as easy as one may think. My wife and I were just truly impressed with his professionalism not making any excuses he had about total 10 burgers or so to make did them all in a timely manner and after making them delivered them to every table with a smile on his face. It's rare that employees go out of there way like that but for those who do gotta give them credit where credit is due. Also gotta add Ryan once things simmered down a bit went to each table to make sure everything came out correctly and made sure that each customer was completely satisfied with there order. So I just wanted to make sure this guy was thanked and keep doing what you do Ryan hope this review brings you as much happiness as your customer service brought to my wife and I thank you for making Chicago a awesome place to visit!!!
